main event: An unidentified object was observed near Cottonwood, Arizona on 27 January 1953.
interesting points: The object was described as domino-shaped and moved at a slow speed, The witness saw it descend in a zig-zag pattern at high speed before disappearing, The object was estimated to be 50 to 75 feet long and 20 to 30 feet wide, There was no sound reported and no lights blinking on the object, The conclusion was made that it was probably a jet aircraft or possibly a meteor.
witness description: The witness was a reliable observer with considerable experience in observing aircraft.
